"نُنْبَغَى","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"1","gen":"-","num":"p"},{"role":"present_1-s","form":"أُنْبَغَى","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"1","gen":"-","num":"s"},{"role":"present_1-p","form":"نَنْبَغِي","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"1","gen":"-","num":"p"},{"role":"present_2-d","form":"تَنْبَغِيا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"-","num":"d"},{"role":"present_2-d","form":"تَنْبَغِيانِ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"-","num":"d"},{"role":"present_1-s","form":"أَنْبَغِي","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"1","gen":"-","num":"s"},{"role":"present_1mp","form":"نَنْبَغ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"present_1ms","form":"أَنْبَغ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"s"}],"frequency_in_corpus":489,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n2961"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A7%D9%90%D9%86%D9%92%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%BA%D9%8E%D9%89"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to beseem, to be proper, to be seemly, to be necessary, must","tags":["past","rare"],"examples":[{"text":"لَا أَعْلَمُ مَاذَا يَنْبَغِي أَنْ أَتَوَقَّعَ مِنْهَا.","english":"I don't know what I should expect from her."},{"text":"اَلظَّاهِرُ أَنَّ «لَهَا» فِي قَوْلِ الْمُتَنَبِّي: «لَوْلَا مُفَارَقَةُ الْأَحْبَابِ مَا وَجَدَتْ * لَهَا الْمَنَايَا إِلَى أَرْوَاحِنَا سُبُلَا» جَارٌّ وَمَجْرُورٌ مُتَعَلِّقٌ بِوَجَدَتْ، لٰكِنَّ فِيهِ تَعَدِّيَ فِعْلِ الظَّاهِرِ إِلَى ضَمِيرِهِ الْمُتَّصِلِ كَقَوْلِكَ «ضَرَبَهُ زَيْدٌ» وَذٰلِكَ مُمْتَنِعٌ؛ فَيَنْبَغِي أَنْ يُقَدَّرَ صِفَةً فِي الْأَصْلِ لِسُبُلَا، فَلَمَّا تَقَدَّمَ عَلَيْهِ صَارَ حَالًا مِنْهُ"}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/in.ba.ɣaː/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n2961","headword_ar":"انبغى","root":"bgY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"is said in the S to be quasi-pass. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bagayotuhu","text_ar":"بَغَيْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ainokasara","text_ar":"اِنْكَسَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kasarotuhu","text_ar":"كَسَرْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and Esh-Shiháb says of the aor. that it is quasi-pass. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bagaAhu","text_ar":"بَغَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yabogiyhi","text_ar":"يَبْغِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Talabahu","text_ar":"طَلَبَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) [Fei says,] it has been asserted that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AnbgY","text_ar":"انبغى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is quasi-pass. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bagaY","text_ar":"بَغَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but a verb of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AnfEl","text_ar":"انفعل"},{"kind":"text","text":"is not used as a quasi-pass. unless it implies effort, and the consequence of an action, as in the case of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kasarotuhu","text_ar":"كَسَرْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", of which the quasi-pass. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ainokasara","text_ar":"اِنْكَسَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AnbgY","text_ar":"انبغى"},{"kind":"text","text":"does not: some, however, allow its being thus used: (Msb:) accord. to Zj, it is as though it were syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AinoTalaba","text_ar":"اِنْطَلَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as quasi-pass. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Talaba","text_ar":"طَلَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, suitable, fit, meet,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proper;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Zj, TA;) [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"right,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"allowable;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"very requisite:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see explanations of exs. following:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it behooved:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, facilitated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"easy;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Er-Rághib, K;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"practicable,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manageable."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Er-Rághib, TA.) Accord. to some, this verb is not used in the pret. tense, but only in the aor.: it is reckoned among verbs imperfectly inflected: (Msb, TA:) but the pret. is mentioned by AZ and Sb and Zj, and by ElKhattábee on the authority of Ks; and was often used by Esh-Sháfi'ee: it is, however, very rare. (TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yanobagiY laka A^ano tafoEala ka*aA","text_ar":"يَنْبَغِى لَكَ اَنْ تَفْعَلَ كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It is suitable to thee,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is fit, meet,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proper,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for thee,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it behooveth thee, that thou shouldst do such a thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, TA.) And, accord. to Zj,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AinobagaY lifulaAnK A^ano yafoEala","text_ar":"اِنْبَغَى لِفُلَانٍ اَنْ يَفْعَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, suitable to such a one,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fit, meet,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proper, for him, that he should do,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to do,"},{"kind":"text","text":"such a thing. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA yanobagiY laka A^ano tafoEala h`*aA","text_ar":"مَا يَنْبَغِى لَكَ اَنْ تَفْعَلَ هٰذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lh, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mA yubotagaY","text_ar":"ما يُبْتَغَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) with fet-h to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"g","text_ar":"غ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mA A@nobagaY","text_ar":"ما ا@نْبَغَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mA A@botugiYa","text_ar":"ما ا@بْتُغِىَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Lh, K;) of which four phrases, the first is given by Lh as explanatory of the third and fourth, and means, accord. to Esh-Shiháb,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It is not right, proper, fit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"meet, nor allowable, for thee that thou shouldst do this,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to do this;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it is not good for thee"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.; but he adds that only the aor. has been heard from the Arabs in this sense. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yanobagiY A^ano yakuwna ka*aA","text_ar":"يَنْبَغِى اَنْ يَكُونَ كَذَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It is very requisite that it should be so,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that such a thing ought be;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it ought to be so,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such a thing ought to be; it behooves that it should be so,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such a thing behooves;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it is not well that such a thing should be neglected,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"left undone."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And Ks is related to have heard, from the Arabs, the phrase,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA yanobagiY A^ano yakuwna ka*aA","text_ar":"مَا يَنْبَغِى اَنْ يَكُونَ كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It is not right that it should be so,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that such a thing should be:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it is not good"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. (Msb.) It is said in the Kur [xxxvi. 69],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wamaA Eal~amonaAhu Al$~iEora wamaA","text_ar":"وَمَا عَلَّمْنَاهُ الشِّعْرَ وَمَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yanobagiY lahu","text_ar":"يَنْبَغِى لَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And we have not taught him poetry,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"versification"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nor is it right, proper, fit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"meet, for him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nor is it easy to him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd, Jel, Er-Rághib,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"practicable to him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd, Er-Rághib.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","Msb","Lh","K","Bd"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}